1
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:12,139
Are you gonna be captain again this year?

2
00:00:12,447 --> 00:00:13,841
Nah, too lazy.

3
00:00:13,980 --> 00:00:16,717
He’s got a nickname Maew. Try calling him that, maybe you’ll get closer.

4
00:00:16,743 --> 00:00:19,493
Meow meow.

5
00:00:20,128 --> 00:00:21,642
Damn, that’s romantic as hell.

6
00:00:21,755 --> 00:00:22,831
Do you bring your girlfriend here often?

7
00:00:23,161 --> 00:00:23,814
I don’t have one.

8
00:00:24,158 --> 00:00:26,045
Someone like you doesn’t have a girlfriend?

9
00:00:26,210 --> 00:00:28,890
- But you can sleep here if you want.
- What about your mom and Nue upstairs?

10
00:00:29,807 --> 00:00:30,640
It’s fine.

11
00:00:31,383 --> 00:00:33,241
Then I’m going to sleep. Goodnight, Tiger.

12
00:00:33,549 --> 00:00:36,442
Suer. You can just call me Suer.

13
00:00:36,567 --> 00:00:40,197
- Then goodnight, Suer.
- Goodnight, Nao.

14
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:43,960
Tiger

15
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:45,240
Tiger

16
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:46,840
Wake up.

17
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:53,600
Sorry.

18
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:55,440
I’m heading out right now.

19
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:59,080
Hey, why are you in such a rush?
Stay and eat with us first.

20
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,360
Uh...

21
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:04,440
It’s okay. I don’t wanna bother you.

22
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:09,720
Hey, why are you rushing off?
Eat with us first.

23
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:15,040
I gotta go run some errands.

24
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:18,280
Thanks for letting me stay over.

25
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:20,680
Yeah.

26
00:01:22,960 --> 00:01:23,720
What errands?

27
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:27,240
What’s with him?

28
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:30,120
I don’t know.

29
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:35,920
Hey, Suer. Did you go home to sleep last night?

30
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:37,360
You didn’t come sleep in my room.

31
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:42,280
Hey guys, do you know Yahyee from room 8?

32
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:45,200
The tiny one?

33
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:46,720
Yeah, that’s the one.

34
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,120
Why?

35
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:49,960
I think I found my first love.

36
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:53,320
Whoa.

37
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:54,640
What’s she like?

38
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:57,760
From what I know, she’s nice.

39
00:01:57,960 --> 00:01:59,080
Friendly too.

40
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,120
And cute.

41
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,120
Really?

42
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,840
Damn it, send it over.

43
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:55,240
Buy me a drink.

44
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,480
What?

45
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,360
Buy me one.

46
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:06,760
Yeah, send it.

47
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:32,080
Ooh, the pork tastes better than the sausage.

48
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,040
Try it.

49
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,360
I’ll be right back.

50
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,040
Where is he going?

51
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:49,080
- My drink.
- Hm?

52
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:50,720
What drink?

53
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,480
Come on.

54
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,160
The one you said you’d buy me.

55
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:57,160
When did I ever say that?

56
00:03:58,840 --> 00:03:59,680
Cheat sheet.

57
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:02,120
Oh.

58
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:04,760
You asshole. Taking advantage during the chaos.

59
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:05,760
What do you want?

60
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:06,920
Same as you.

61
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:08,520
What drink would you like?

62
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:09,680
- Same as me?
- Yeah.

63
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:12,280
- Two red sodas, please.
- Sure.

64
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:15,080
So, this morning...

65
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:17,280
where were you rushing off to without eating first?

66
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:22,560
So are you sleeping at my place again tonight?

67
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,840
Here you go.

68
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,520
Thank you.

69
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:35,800
You made me buy the drinks and now carry them too?

70
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,480
You’ve got it easy, asshole.

71
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:40,960
Yeah.

72
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:45,960
About what you asked me earlier... if I’d stay at your place.

73
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,080
Can I really?

74
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:51,720
My mom said yes. The question is whether you want to be there or not.

75
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:53,840
Then...

76
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:56,840
Can I pack my stuff and move into your place?

77
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,760
- Of course.
- Really?

78
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,200
Yeah.

79
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,120
Like, permanently.

80
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,960
Yeah, do whatever the hell you want.

81
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,080
I’m hungry now.

82
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,240
Hey, which one’s yours?

83
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,160
Alright, bye.

84
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:54,920
Whoa, Mom. You cooked so much.

85
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:58,560
Well, you said your friend’s staying over.

86
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,680
So I cooked extra for him.

87
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:05,320
Mom, only one friend is coming. Not the whole class.

88
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:08,320
Well, I didn’t know.

89
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:09,800
And I already cooked it all.

90
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,720
It’s good to have plenty.

91
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,520
In case it’s not enough.

92
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:16,000
Alright, alright.

93
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:19,800
Doesn’t it look delicious?

94
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:21,160
It looks amazing.

95
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,760
- I wanna eat already.
- Nao.

96
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,080
Oh, looks like my friend’s here.

97
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,280
Hey.

98
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:34,520
Damn.

99
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:37,080
So you’re really moving in with me?

100
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,760
Huh?

101
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:41,000
Weren’t you the one who said I could?

102
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,120
See?

103
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,160
Yeah, you can.

104
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:47,640
Put your bag over there and come eat.

105
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:59,400
Why are you standing there like an idiot? Come eat.

106
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:00,960
Or did you already eat?

107
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:04,600
Is this really okay?

108
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:07,080
Of course. My mom cooked a ton.

109
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,920
It’d be a waste if you didn’t eat.

110
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:12,080
Come on.

111
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,400
Let’s go.

112
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,360
What are you guys doing?

113
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,600
We’re checking if there’s enough food.

114
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:25,160
I was thinking of making more.

115
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:28,040
That’s enough, Mom. There’s already a lot.

116
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:30,720
Make yourself at home, okay?

117
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:32,560
Here.

118
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:33,720
This one.

119
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,960
I just fried these fresh.

120
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:37,480
Thank you.

121
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,640
Nice and crispy.

122
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:40,440
Thank you.

123
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,120
Thank you.

124
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:45,480
Is something wrong, dear?

125
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,000
Are you feeling sick?

126
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,600
- Should I make you some porridge?
- Oh, no. I’m fine.

127
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:53,520
Then...

128
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:55,200
Try this curry.

129
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,880
It’s Southern-style curry.

130
00:08:58,280 --> 00:08:58,960
Okay.

131
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:03,880
Duennao, get some vegetables for Tiger too.

132
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:07,280
He can get them himself, Mom. He’s sitting right there.

133
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:11,200
Come on. It’s not often we have guests over.

134
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:17,240
Just so you know, we don’t normally cook this much at my house.

135
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,800
My mom went all out because you’re here.

136
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:22,960
Come on, eat.

137
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:25,280
Hey, Duen,

138
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:26,360
Dan,

139
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:28,520
school’s been open for a while now.

140
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:31,480
How’s studying going? No one’s told me anything.

141
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:35,440
- Is it hard?
- Not really.

142
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,040
It’s going well.

143
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,120
Suer.

144
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:41,320
How’s school for you?

145
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:43,840
It’s whatever.

146
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:50,320
I didn’t ask just to get that kind of answer.

147
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,120
Sit down.

148
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,840
When are you gonna stop acting like this?

149
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:13,520
Try learning from your brother.

150
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,480
Be more like him.

151
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:23,560
- No thanks.
- Stop acting so childish already.

152
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,080
I’ve...

153
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:28,440
been lenient with you long enough.

154
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:32,800
Suer.

155
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,120
Suer.

156
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:38,880
You okay?

157
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,440
I was just lost in thought.

158
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,120
Mm.

159
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,080
Keep eating.

160
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:54,440
School’s really hard, Mom.

161
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:55,720
I don’t get any of it.

162
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:57,760
Physics, chemistry, biology...

163
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:01,800
- I don’t understand anything.
- Just like me when I was studying.

164
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:05,120
I didn’t understand why we had to study some things either.
Especially in high school.

165
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,640
I was terrible.

166
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:08,160
It was so hard.

167
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:09,280
I even...

168
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:12,480
copied my friend’s exam answers and got caught.

169
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:15,000
Seriously, Mom?

170
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,360
Seriously.

171
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,960
Good thing I were well-behaved.

172
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:21,440
That’s why the teacher let me pass.

173
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:24,720
No, honestly, the teacher was probably too lazy to fix my failing grade.

174
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:25,960
I know.

175
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,240
You almost couldn’t continue studying.

176
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,120
What about you, Suer?

177
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:35,080
I heard you’re in the advanced math class.

178
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,600
The schedule sounds brutal as hell.

179
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:41,600
Tiger.

180
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:43,680
You’re in the advanced math class, dear?

181
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:45,400
How is it? Is it hard?

182
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:48,240
It’s alright.

183
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,480
There’s a lot of work.

184
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:52,600
And tons of homework too.

185
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:54,440
Even though school just started.

186
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:57,920
Wow, honestly...

187
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:01,400
teachers should just give a reasonable amount of homework. I don’t know why they assign so much.

188
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:05,520
But you’re really amazing for getting into that special class.

189
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:06,800
Thank you.

190
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:10,920
Come on, let’s eat.

191
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,360
No point talking about stressful stuff.

192
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:18,040
Here, let me tell you something. Don’t bother with physics.

193
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:20,040
Just guess randomly.

194
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:26,320
- Is it a living thing?
- No.

195
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:27,720
Is it food?

196
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:30,160
Nope.

197
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:33,440
Is it something we use?

198
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:36,880
- Yeah, it’s an item. You use it every day.
- Ahh.

199
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:38,720
I use it every day?

200
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:41,840
- Balloon.
- Yea... okay.

201
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:44,080
- Second only to the king of the jungle.
- Tiger?

202
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:45,240
Tiger?

203
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:48,720
Very smart, dear. See? You’re smart too.

204
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:56,400
Eat slowly or you’ll choke.

205
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,480
Thank you.

206
00:12:58,160 --> 00:13:00,440
Can Tiger eat this, dear?

207
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:02,320
- This one’s delicious.
- I think so.

208
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:03,400
This looks tasty.

209
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:05,960
Duen, use a spoon.

210
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:08,880
Too late.

211
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,440
Already did it.

212
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:16,760
And then you’ll complain again if he chokes.

213
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:30,640
Suer.

214
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:36,120
Go do something else. Go on, I’ll clean this up myself.

215
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:44,200
Wake up already!

216
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:45,280
Hey!

217
00:13:47,040 --> 00:13:49,040
- Ouch.
- Come on, get up.

218
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,120
Play properly.

219
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:55,640
What?

220
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,600
Dude, you’re the problem.

221
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:58,720
We’re gonna lose.

222
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:09,920
Hey!

223
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:15,560
Hey, wait for me!

224
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:35,680
Suer.

225
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,520
I’ve been wanting to ask you this.

226
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,240
Where do you buy your clothes?

227
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:40,440
I like them.

228
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:43,160
- These?
- Yeah.

229
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:44,680
I don’t know.

230
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:46,280
I didn’t buy them myself.

231
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,720
Why? You want some?

232
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:51,000
Yeah, I wanna wear stuff like that too.

233
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:53,880
I can give you some later.

234
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,240
Really?

235
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:57,960
You said it, okay?

236
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,480
Yeah.

237
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:02,720
I’ll remember that.

238
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:05,960
See you tonight.

239
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:16,800
No, but when’s he coming?

240
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:21,840
- No idea.
- Damn, speak of the devil. Looking handsome as ever too.

241
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:25,640
Hey, dude.

242
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:32,440
Why do you seem so close to the twins lately?

243
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:37,520
No way. The one I’m close with is Nao.

244
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:39,720
Not really Nue.

245
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,160
Why?

246
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:44,680
Nothing. I just noticed you barely sleep in my room anymore.

247
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:48,440
Hey, you miss me or what?

248
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:49,360
Damn.

249
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:53,200
I was gonna say it’s a good thing, asshole. You’re annoying.

250
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:56,560
My room’s tiny already, and you still steal my room space.

251
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:59,400
Wait, Suer. You’ve been sleeping at Nao’s house?

252
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:00,600
Yeah.

253
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:03,280
I found new friends already. Bye.

254
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,720
You assholes.

255
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:08,600
You sleep over there this often and they don’t mind?

256
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:10,760
Not really.

257
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,840
They actually welcome me.

258
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:16,880
Come on, I know you’ve got a plan, Suer.

259
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:17,920
What fucking plan?

260
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:20,520
Getting close through the younger brother.

261
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:23,040
Truth is, you like Dannue, right?

262
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:25,480
Wait, so this was all your plan?

263
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:29,320
Damn it, idiot. Nothing at all.

264
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:31,400
I just like being there, that’s all.

265
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:35,880
So, is Dannue cute?

266
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:43,240
Why?

267
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:44,400
Do you like him?

268
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,320
What? No.

269
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:48,680
Why would I?

270
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:52,320
Wait, do you two like the same person?

271
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:55,720
I don’t like anyone.

272
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:58,680
Or do you like Nao?

273
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:03,680
I don’t have anything going on with either twin. I just...

274
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:06,160
don’t wanna steal Field’s room anymore.

275
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:07,880
You just realized that?

276
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:15,480
Or maybe you still don’t understand your own feelings?

277
00:17:22,120 --> 00:17:22,880
Shit.

278
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:32,240
Hey!

279
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:37,920
Yay!

280
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:47,400
Alright, everyone.

281
00:17:47,840 --> 00:17:50,000
You all did really well today.

282
00:17:50,520 --> 00:17:54,040
I want everyone to remember the good feelings from today.

283
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:55,640
Because soon...

284
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:59,520
we’ll have a football tournament
to build relationships with other schools.

285
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:01,280
Get yourselves ready.

286
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,320
Competing with those schools?

287
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:07,160
I think you guys should start training in boxing instead.

288
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:09,120
Why?

289
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:10,920
You guys probably don’t know this yet.

290
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:14,760
This “friendly football tournament” might sound nice,

291
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:17,640
but we actually compete against schools that always pick fights with us.

292
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:20,120
And most of the time...

293
00:18:20,520 --> 00:18:22,480
they don’t really play by the rules.

294
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:24,600
Shit.

295
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,640
Then what are we supposed to do?

296
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:33,680
Why be scared when we’ve got the gang leader right here?

297
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:35,560
What gang leader?

298
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:37,200
What the hell does that have to do with me?

299
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:38,480
Come on.

300
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:46,440
Tiger.

301
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:50,200
Until the competition day comes, you’ll probably have it rough.

302
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:54,240
But I want you to do your best as captain.

303
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:55,320
Yes, sir.

304
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,360
- My friend’s awesome.
- My friend?

305
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:03,240
Yeah, your friend.

306
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:12,280
Do you think this whole friendly football thing is really that serious?

307
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:15,440
Like what Micky said.

308
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:17,520
He’s not completely wrong.

309
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:19,960
There are some rough players.

310
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:22,280
But it’s not that bad.

311
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:25,200
Why? Are you scared?

312
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:27,360
Just listen to you guys talking.

313
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:28,520
Jeez.

314
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:30,680
It’s nothing.

315
00:19:30,840 --> 00:19:33,600
Or even if something happens, I’ll handle it myself.

316
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:35,320
Oh?

317
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:38,560
Does being team captain weigh on you that much?

318
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:43,120
So don’t worry about it.

319
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,480
If anything happens,

320
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:47,240
I’ll take care of everything.

321
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:50,800
Mm.

322
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:53,280
So, how long have you been playing football?

323
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:57,160
Quite a long time.

324
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:58,400
Why?

325
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:01,920
Nothing. Just asking. You’re really good.

326
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:03,720
I saw Coach praising you too.

327
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:09,520
Have you never thought about taking it seriously?

328
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:12,520
I think you can do it.

329
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,040
What about you?

330
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:26,240
What?

331
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:30,600
Your dream.

332
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:32,480
What is it?

333
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:35,080
My dream?

334
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:37,440
I wanna be a professional football player.

335
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:40,400
But if that doesn’t work out, then maybe engineering.

336
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:41,760
Engineering?

337
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:43,680
Why?

338
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:51,840
Because my dad’s an engineer.

339
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:59,040
What about you? What do you wanna do?

340
00:21:00,040 --> 00:21:01,520
I have no idea.

341
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:06,040
If I could choose,

342
00:21:06,560 --> 00:21:08,880
I’d probably want a life of my own.

343
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:11,600
Huh? What did you say?

344
00:21:14,040 --> 00:21:15,120
Nothing.

345
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:18,920
Hey, can I ask you something?

346
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:23,160
Auntie Maew and your dad...

347
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:24,960
how did they meet?

348
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:29,560
Hmm. Why do you suddenly wanna know?

349
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:32,480
Just curious.

350
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:35,920
Alright. If you wanna know, I’ll tell you.

351
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:50,000
My dad...

352
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,600
was born into

353
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:54,360
a pretty wealthy family.

354
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:59,160
As for my mom, she was just an ordinary woman.
The two of them

355
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:00,840
met at university.

356
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:06,640
My dad was super popular,
and my mom was beautiful and kind.

357
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:10,360
A lot of guys were after her,

358
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:12,320
including my dad.

359
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:17,200
My dad chased after her for a really long time before she finally gave in.

360
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:20,400
That’s how they ended up together.

361
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:24,920
But my dad’s family was against my mom.

362
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:27,320
Because my dad already had a fiancée.

363
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:29,480
Back then,

364
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:31,840
my dad had a huge fight with his family.

365
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:34,080
So he decided

366
00:22:34,440 --> 00:22:39,520
to leave and start a new life with my mom from scratch.
Then we came along.

367
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:43,320
I...

368
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:45,600
Can I ask something else?

369
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:47,120
About why...

370
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:49,640
Mm.

371
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:54,480
Life was going pretty well until I was in grade 8.

372
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,440
My dad got cancer.

373
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:02,840
So we used all the money our family had to pay for his treatment.

374
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:04,920
But in the end,

375
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:06,920
my dad died.

376
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:10,240
And my family fell into debt.

377
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:16,000
Hey... I...

378
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:18,000
I’m sorry.

379
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:22,640
Mm. It’s okay. I’m fine talking about it.

380
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:24,520
Then...

381
00:23:25,760 --> 00:23:27,600
what did your family do after that?

382
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:36,920
A man entered our lives.

383
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:40,440
His name was Chat.

384
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:43,960
He said he’d liked my mom for a long time.

385
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:47,360
He wanted to take care of my family in my dad’s place.

386
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,640
He paid off all our debts.

387
00:23:55,360 --> 00:23:58,040
In the end, my mom decided to marry him.

388
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:02,240
If my mom hadn’t made that decision,

389
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:07,960
- those loan sharks would've kept coming after us.
- Then where is he now?

390
00:24:12,080 --> 00:24:13,400
They’re not together anymore.

391
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:18,240
That’s basically my parents’ story.

392
00:24:18,880 --> 00:24:20,240
I’m gonna head upstairs now.

393
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:22,000
Mm.

394
00:24:23,080 --> 00:24:24,560
Thanks for telling me.

395
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:27,320
It’s okay. I wanted to.

396
00:24:55,680 --> 00:24:56,600
Hey.

397
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:02,000
Nao.

398
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:05,960
Nao.

399
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:07,080
What is it?

400
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:10,560
What’s wrong with you?

401
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:13,760
Nothing.

402
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:17,160
Duennao, what’s wrong?

403
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:20,440
A spider.

404
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:22,680
Huh?

405
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:26,240
- A spider?
- Duen’s scared of spiders.

406
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:28,000
I’ll take care of it.

407
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:37,640
All done.

408
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:39,080
I chased it away.

409
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:41,800
Dan’s amazing. Dan’s the best.

410
00:25:43,640 --> 00:25:45,520
I’m gonna go to sleep now.

411
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:47,720
Sorry Duennao startled you.

412
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:48,960
It’s okay.

413
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:55,720
You’re scared of spiders?

414
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:57,000
I just found out.

415
00:25:58,680 --> 00:25:59,800
I’m not scared.

416
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,480
But don’t you dare tell anyone.

417
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:03,640
Got it?

418
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:05,760
Yeah, I won’t.

419
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:29,400
Pork with garlic, but no garlic.

420
00:26:29,560 --> 00:26:32,120
And a fried egg that’s fully cooked but still runny.

421
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:39,720
Why do I keep seeing you at Nao’s house lately?

422
00:26:40,080 --> 00:26:42,200
Don’t tell me you’re trying to hit on Nue too.

423
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:43,160
Hm?

424
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:45,680
What did you just say?

425
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:49,760
Suer, you...

426
00:26:50,120 --> 00:26:51,320
What?

427
00:26:51,840 --> 00:26:53,080
Why are you looking at me like that?

428
00:26:53,760 --> 00:26:56,200
Suer, you bastard.

429
00:26:57,480 --> 00:27:01,480
Don’t you think it’s weird
that a guy like Suer is clinging to you guys like a leech?

430
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:03,520
If it’s not because he likes Nue.

431
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:08,440
At first, I didn’t think so.

432
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:11,360
But now I’m starting to.

433
00:27:14,320 --> 00:27:16,680
You guys are getting ridiculous. Shut up already, asshole.

434
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:18,840
Tell me the truth.

435
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:19,800
Here.

436
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:21,760
Spill it.

437
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:25,760
Suer.

438
00:27:26,360 --> 00:27:27,480
You dog-faced idiot.

439
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:29,520
You like my brother, don’t you?

440
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:33,200
I’ll burn your eyelashes off with a lighter while you sleep.

441
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:35,080
Can you stop getting carried away?

442
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:37,280
At first, I didn’t suspect you either.

443
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:39,440
But now I’m starting to.

444
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:41,760
This is all part of your master plan, right?

445
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:42,880
Isn’t it?

446
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:45,520
What master plan? I told you it’s not like that.

447
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:48,160
I don’t think you’re a bad person or anything.

448
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:50,560
I’m giving you a chance to prove yourself.

449
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,440
No.

450
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:55,200
I don’t need a chance.

451
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:56,640
Okay?

452
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:04,320
Suer.

453
00:28:05,040 --> 00:28:07,960
You’re really gonna throw away the best chance I’ve ever given you?

454
00:28:08,800 --> 00:28:10,040
I can tell that you’re...

455
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:12,120
not like everyone else.

456
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:15,760
You idiot. Dumb idiot.

457
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:22,400
I don’t like Nue.

458
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:24,800
Do you understand?

459
00:28:30,040 --> 00:28:31,080
I don’t believe you.

460
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,520
I know my brother is...

461
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:36,800
too cute to resist, right?

462
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:42,360
Wait a second.

463
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:44,960
You said your brother is cute?

464
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:50,480
Then that means you’re cute too.

465
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:52,000
Hm?

466
00:29:11,040 --> 00:29:13,200
Who the hell eats and doesn’t clean up after themselves?

467
00:29:14,040 --> 00:29:15,160
You, maybe?

468
00:29:15,480 --> 00:29:17,760
Whoa, I never do that.

469
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:20,520
Damn, right? Don’t you think?

470
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:22,800
But you should...

471
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:24,160
hurry up and work.

472
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:30,320
Come on, hurry up!

473
00:29:32,160 --> 00:29:34,680
This punishment is all your fault.

474
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:39,480
How is it my fault? You’re the one talking nonsense.

475
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:43,280
As compensation for getting me punished,

476
00:29:44,120 --> 00:29:46,560
I demand emotional damages.

477
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:48,680
Hey.

478
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:53,520
Do you know Berry Bear Café around the corner?

479
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:54,600
Why?

480
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:59,800
Their bingsu is really good,
and they’ve got a new menu today.

481
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,960
Plus, there’s a one-day discount.

482
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:09,680
- So?
- Their strawberry smoothie is amazing too. It’s my favorite.

483
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:14,480
It’d be nice if I got to have some.

484
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:18,560
So you want me to treat you?

485
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:23,480
- Yeah, I’ll treat you.
- Really?

486
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:26,280
Yes!

487
00:30:27,240 --> 00:30:29,040
You really are a wonderful friend.

488
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:32,200
My best friend. The best friend in the world.

489
00:30:34,600 --> 00:30:35,480
Pick up the trash.

490
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:38,080
- Pick it up.
- I’m too lazy already.

491
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:41,440
Are we even gonna make it to class?

492
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:46,440
Yeah. Let’s go.

493
00:31:08,480 --> 00:31:10,120
This is my regular table, you know.

494
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,560
Order whatever you want. Don’t hold back.

495
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:15,640
Wow, maybe I should hold back for my own sake.

496
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:19,200
What should we get? Bingsu?

497
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:20,760
Up to you.

498
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:24,920
Bingsu.

499
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:35,080
Hey, why’d you order so much?

500
00:31:35,800 --> 00:31:36,720
Can you even finish all that?

501
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:39,280
Of course.

502
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:41,720
I’ve been starving for ages.

503
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:44,680
I thought you came here often.

504
00:31:45,040 --> 00:31:46,400
You said you liked it, didn’t you?

505
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:48,400
Only once in a while.

506
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:57,000
It’s expensive. I usually spend all my money on games.

507
00:31:57,160 --> 00:32:01,520
I do want sweets,
but games are more important.

508
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:04,760
Since you ordered this much, you better finish it all.

509
00:32:05,280 --> 00:32:09,040
Yeah, I know. Some of it I’m taking home too.

510
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:10,680
For Mom and Dan.

511
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:29,080
If you drink coffee now, when are you even gonna sleep?

512
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:32,560
I’m used to it already.

513
00:32:40,680 --> 00:32:41,520
Aren’t you gonna eat?

514
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:44,280
I’m not really into sweets.

515
00:32:45,680 --> 00:32:46,680
Here, try it.

516
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:50,600
At first, I didn’t like it either.

517
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,440
But just try it first.

518
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:03,640
So?

519
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:06,040
- It’s actually pretty good.
- See?

520
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:23,600
You eat like such a mess.

521
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:24,320
Here.

522
00:33:32,560 --> 00:33:33,640
Help me eat some.

523
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:35,920
What?

524
00:33:36,360 --> 00:33:37,640
You ordered it, so finish it.

525
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:39,200
Suer.

526
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:41,640
You ordered it, so you eat it.

527
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,240
Take responsibility.

528
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:44,760
Then should we pack it to go?

529
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:47,000
How are you supposed to pack bingsu to go?

530
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:48,360
Finish it.

531
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:51,400
Fine.

532
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:02,200
I’m so freaking full.

533
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:04,640
Well, look at how much you ate.

534
00:34:05,520 --> 00:34:07,600
Thanks for the treat.

535
00:34:10,640 --> 00:34:11,640
Hey, Nao.

536
00:34:12,040 --> 00:34:13,240
Can you get home by yourself?

537
00:34:13,680 --> 00:34:14,720
What the hell?

538
00:34:15,080 --> 00:34:18,000
- You’re ditching me after treating me?
- No.

539
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:20,520
I just need to go home and grab that shirt.

540
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:23,240
The one you said looked good.

541
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:25,760
You still want it or not?

542
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:28,760
Seriously?

543
00:34:31,320 --> 00:34:33,200
It’d be a waste not to wear it.

544
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:36,440
Alright.

545
00:34:36,720 --> 00:34:37,920
My place is really close anyway.

546
00:34:38,240 --> 00:34:41,360
I go back all the time. It’s easy, chill.

547
00:34:42,640 --> 00:34:43,680
See you at home then.

548
00:34:44,440 --> 00:34:45,240
- Okay.
- Let’s go.

549
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:43,200
No manners at all?

550
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:47,240
Looks like a lot of stuff’s gone missing.

551
00:35:50,200 --> 00:35:51,000
How would you know?

552
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:52,920
Did you sneak into my room?

553
00:35:57,840 --> 00:35:59,080
I need to talk to you.

554
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:03,880
Back when you were staying with Field,

555
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:06,200
you still came home sometimes.

556
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:11,120
But lately you barely come home anymore. What’s that supposed to mean?

557
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:14,240
It doesn’t mean anything.

558
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:18,320
Suer.

559
00:36:19,640 --> 00:36:21,840
Looks like you really like it there.

560
00:36:25,680 --> 00:36:28,520
Do those people even know you’re mafia?

561
00:36:33,680 --> 00:36:35,640
I think you forgot something.

562
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:42,040
What?

563
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,240
What are you doing, Duen?

564
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:57,240
Waiting for Suer.

565
00:37:02,280 --> 00:37:03,160
Here.

566
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:04,720
Take it.

567
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:06,880
What is it?

568
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:09,040
Open it.

569
00:37:10,680 --> 00:37:11,680
Hmm?

570
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:16,760
What is all this, honey?

571
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:20,760
All of this is for me?

572
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:22,440
Yeah.

573
00:37:27,720 --> 00:37:28,720
Whoa.

574
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,400
This one looks nice.

575
00:37:31,720 --> 00:37:33,440
You can try it on.

576
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,440
What do you think, Mom? Dan?

577
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:41,840
- Does it suit me?
- It really does.

578
00:37:41,840 --> 00:37:43,880
It looks expensive too.

579
00:37:44,240 --> 00:37:46,440
Are you sure it’s okay to give it to Duen?

580
00:37:47,640 --> 00:37:48,600
Of course.

581
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:52,960
Otherwise it’d probably stay in my closet forever.

582
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:01,680
This one’s nice too.

583
00:38:03,080 --> 00:38:04,080
Try it.

584
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:06,520
Hey, it suits Dan.

585
00:38:06,760 --> 00:38:08,920
Really? I think it’s a little too big.

586
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:12,480
It suits you more.

587
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:10,240
Don’t you feel bad for them? If they end up getting dragged into trouble because of you.

588
00:39:10,840 --> 00:39:13,800
No matter what, you can’t run from the fact that you’re the son of a mafia.

589
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:16,600
I’m warning you.

590
00:39:17,120 --> 00:39:19,200
You should back off now while you still can.

591
00:39:20,320 --> 00:39:21,920
Before you’re the one who gets betrayed.

592
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:25,680
If you really care about them,

593
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:30,800
shouldn’t you think about their safety first?

594
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:33,800
You should end it now.

595
00:39:47,240 --> 00:39:48,080
Hey.

596
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:51,880
What the hell, man?

597
00:39:52,040 --> 00:39:53,520
You scared the shit out of me.

598
00:39:54,080 --> 00:39:55,160
Why aren’t you asleep?

599
00:39:57,200 --> 00:39:59,520
I’m not sleepy.

600
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:01,720
What about you? Why are you sitting here in the dark?

601
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:03,920
I can’t sleep.

602
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:07,840
Well no shit, you drank a ton of coffee earlier.

603
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:09,760
And you still had the nerve to say you were used to it.

604
00:40:11,880 --> 00:40:13,920
What about you? Why aren’t you sleeping?

605
00:40:15,160 --> 00:40:16,280
I’m hungry.

606
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:19,320
- I was thinking of going to the night market.
- Hungry?

607
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:24,080
- You’re still hungry after eating all that?
- Yeah, well, since we’re already up...

608
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:25,480
Wanna come with me?

609
00:40:29,080 --> 00:40:30,280
I’m gonna grab a jacket first.

610
00:40:31,320 --> 00:40:32,720
Hey, you forgot this.

611
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:50,280
Come on, let’s go back.

612
00:40:54,400 --> 00:40:55,400
Suer.

613
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:56,640
What?

614
00:41:01,880 --> 00:41:04,600
Shit. Go, go, go!

615
00:41:04,680 --> 00:41:06,960
Hey, Tiger! I remember you! Where are you going?

616
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:09,760
Go!

617
00:41:10,080 --> 00:41:11,200
Hurry up, Nao!

618
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:14,560
Over here, quick!

619
00:41:19,920 --> 00:41:21,280
Where the hell did he go?

620
00:41:21,360 --> 00:41:22,680
That guy’s freaking fast.

621
00:41:31,080 --> 00:41:32,480
Do you think that asshole saw us?

622
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:35,840
Probably not.

623
00:41:41,560 --> 00:41:42,680
So what do we do now?

624
00:41:42,920 --> 00:41:44,120
Should we call the cops?

625
00:41:44,600 --> 00:41:46,320
Let them leave first, then we’ll call.

626
00:41:50,960 --> 00:41:52,200
Are you scared?

627
00:41:53,400 --> 00:41:54,560
Scared of what?

628
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:56,400
Wow.

629
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:59,600
You totally don’t look scared at all. You’re sweating like crazy.

630
00:42:01,160 --> 00:42:04,720
Shit, running from them felt like being in a movie. Good thing he didn’t pull a gun on us.

631
00:42:12,120 --> 00:42:13,640
My gui chai.

632
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:15,360
Can I even still eat that?

633
00:42:18,920 --> 00:42:20,080
Come on, let’s get back to my bike.

634
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:30,040
Good thing it wasn’t near the house.

635
00:42:47,840 --> 00:42:49,160
Damn.

636
00:42:49,320 --> 00:42:51,240
My gui chai got totally smashed.

637
00:42:52,560 --> 00:42:53,960
Can’t be helped.

638
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:18,920
It’s fine. Still tastes good.

639
00:43:24,920 --> 00:43:25,720
Want some?

640
00:43:27,200 --> 00:43:28,000
Hold on.

641
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:46,600
Go home.

642
00:43:47,720 --> 00:43:48,360
No.

643
00:43:49,360 --> 00:43:50,640
Come work with me.

644
00:43:52,400 --> 00:43:53,320
Dad’s orders.

645
00:43:53,720 --> 00:43:57,600
If you’re not here in twenty minutes, I’ll send people to drag you here myself.

646
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:10,640
I’m heading out for a bit.

647
00:44:11,840 --> 00:44:13,280
Where are you going? You haven’t even eaten yet.

648
00:44:14,600 --> 00:44:15,520
Something urgent came up.

649
00:44:16,560 --> 00:44:17,760
Are you coming back?

650
00:44:22,360 --> 00:44:23,040
Yeah.

651
00:44:24,720 --> 00:44:26,760
Alright then, I’ll stay up and open the door for you.

652
00:44:27,560 --> 00:44:29,280
It’s okay. If you’re sleepy, just sleep.

653
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:31,720
Nah, I stay up late anyway.

654
00:44:31,800 --> 00:44:33,200
I can just play games while I wait.

655
00:44:36,520 --> 00:44:38,200
Okay then.

656
00:44:38,720 --> 00:44:40,520
- I’ll hurry back.
- Yeah.

657
00:45:22,400 --> 00:45:23,320
Go change your clothes.

658
00:45:24,720 --> 00:45:27,640
- I’m not going.
- Go change your clothes.

659
00:47:14,200 --> 00:47:15,760
Hey, Suer.

660
00:47:16,280 --> 00:47:17,440
What happened to you?

661
00:47:18,760 --> 00:47:19,920
Whose blood is that?

662
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:21,760
Is it yours?

663
00:47:22,920 --> 00:47:24,160
Are you hurt anywhere?

664
00:47:26,440 --> 00:47:28,040
Let me see the wound.

665
00:47:34,720 --> 00:47:35,960
Are you okay?

666
00:47:37,800 --> 00:47:39,040
Should we go to the hospital?

667
00:47:42,760 --> 00:47:43,680
Nao.

668
00:47:45,880 --> 00:47:46,720
What?

669
00:47:47,840 --> 00:47:48,560
I...

670
00:47:52,680 --> 00:47:54,520
I already did it.

671
00:47:58,640 --> 00:48:00,400
I did it, Nao.

672
00:48:01,640 --> 00:48:04,280
I didn’t mean to.

673
00:48:07,120 --> 00:48:09,640
I didn’t want to do it, but I did.

674
00:48:12,160 --> 00:48:13,520
I’m sorry.

675
00:48:14,800 --> 00:48:15,840
It’s okay.

676
00:48:19,680 --> 00:48:22,800
If you’re not ready to talk, you can tell me later.

677
00:48:27,560 --> 00:48:28,840
I’m sorry.

678
00:48:32,040 --> 00:48:34,320
Nao, I’m sorry.

679
00:48:37,360 --> 00:48:38,520
It’s okay.

680
00:48:40,400 --> 00:48:42,000
I’m here now.

681
00:49:03,640 --> 00:49:06,200
Nao, why aren’t you asking me anything?

682
00:49:06,360 --> 00:49:08,720
You came back looking like that. What am I even supposed to ask?

683
00:49:08,800 --> 00:49:10,880
Suer, I really like having you around.

684
00:49:11,040 --> 00:49:12,880
The atmosphere’s way more lively with you here.

685
00:49:13,040 --> 00:49:16,360
So no matter what happens, you can always come back here.

686
00:49:16,480 --> 00:49:18,080
How much do you know about that kid’s family?

687
00:49:18,200 --> 00:49:18,920
Why?

688
00:49:19,000 --> 00:49:20,920
You’re not planning to do something weird, are you?

689
00:49:21,120 --> 00:49:22,160
What the hell are you talking about?

690
00:49:22,320 --> 00:49:23,560
You can leave after this.

691
00:49:24,120 --> 00:49:25,000
Kill him.

692
00:49:25,320 --> 00:49:26,640
Why me?

693
00:49:27,120 --> 00:49:29,120
I said shoot him.
